sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant FE as React Frontend<br/>(Vite + React 19)
    participant Clerk as Clerk
    participant API as Express API<br/>(Railway)
    participant DB as Neon PostgreSQL<br/>(+ pgvector)
    participant R2 as Cloudflare R2
    participant Redis as BullMQ / Redis<br/>(Upstash)
    participant Worker as Ingestion Worker
    participant OpenAI as OpenAI API<br/>(Embeddings)
    participant LLM as LLM Provider<br/>(Anthropic / OpenAI / Google)
    participant LF as LangFuse

    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    %% 1. AUTHENTICATION
    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    rect rgb(220, 235, 255)
        Note over User,Clerk: 1 · AUTHENTICATION
        User->>FE: Visit app (unauthenticated)
        FE->>Clerk: Redirect to hosted sign-in UI
        User->>Clerk: Submit credentials (email / OAuth)
        Clerk-->>FE: Session JWT (short-lived token)
        FE->>API: GET /api/v1/users/me  [Bearer JWT]
        API->>Clerk: clerkMiddleware() — verify & decode JWT
        Clerk-->>API: { userId: clerk_xxx }
        API->>DB: UPSERT Users ON CONFLICT clerk_user_id
        Note right of DB: Syncs email + display_name<br/>from Clerk on every /me call
        DB-->>API: User row (internal UUID)
        API-->>FE: { user }
        FE-->>User: Redirect → /documents
    end

    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    %% 2. DOCUMENT UPLOAD
    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    rect rgb(255, 243, 220)
        Note over User,Redis: 2 · DOCUMENT UPLOAD  (presigned URL pattern)
        User->>FE: Drag & drop PDF onto UploadZone
        FE->>API: POST /api/v1/documents/upload-url<br/>{ name, fileName, fileSizeBytes, mimeType }
        API->>API: Zod: mimeType = application/pdf only<br/>fileSizeBytes ≤ 50 MB
        API->>DB: INSERT Documents (status = pending)
        Note right of DB: r2Key = docs/{userId}/{docId}{ext}
        API->>R2: getSignedUrl(PutObjectCommand, 1 hr)
        R2-->>API: Presigned PUT URL
        API-->>FE: { documentId, uploadUrl }

        FE->>R2: PUT <presigned URL>  (PDF binary stream)
        Note right of R2: Direct browser → R2 upload<br/>API never touches the bytes
        R2-->>FE: 200 OK

        FE->>API: POST /api/v1/documents/:id/confirm
        API->>DB: WHERE id = docId AND user_id = userId
        DB-->>API: Document row (ownership verified)
        API->>DB: UPDATE Documents SET status = processing
        API->>Redis: queue.add('ingest', { documentId, userId, r2Key })
        Redis-->>API: Job enqueued (3 retries, exp. backoff)
        API-->>FE: { document: { status: "processing" } }
        FE-->>User: Show processing spinner on document card
    end

    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    %% 3. INGESTION WORKER  (async, separate process)
    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    rect rgb(220, 255, 230)
        Note over Redis,DB: 3 · INGESTION WORKER  (async — Railway worker dyno)
        Redis->>Worker: Dequeue job { documentId, userId, r2Key }
        Worker->>R2: downloadObject(r2Key) → Buffer
        R2-->>Worker: PDF bytes

        Worker->>Worker: pdf-parse(buffer) → { text, numpages }

        alt PDF has no extractable text
            Worker->>DB: UPDATE Documents SET status = failed
            Worker->>Redis: Mark job failed → retry up to 3×
        else Text extracted
            Worker->>Worker: RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter<br/>chunkSize=2048 chars, overlap=200

            loop Batches of 100 chunks
                Worker->>OpenAI: embedTexts(batch)<br/>model: text-embedding-3-small
                OpenAI-->>Worker: number[][] (1536-dim vectors)
            end

            Worker->>DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
            Note right of DB: Bulk INSERT DocumentChunks<br/>(content, embedding::vector, user_id, chunk_index)<br/>in batches of 50 rows
            Worker->>DB: UPDATE Documents SET status = ready, page_count = N
            Worker->>DB: COMMIT
            DB-->>Worker: OK
            Worker->>Redis: Mark job completed
            Note over FE,DB: Frontend polls GET /api/v1/documents<br/>and reflects status = ready
        end

        opt Job exhausts all retries
            Redis->>Worker: Final failure event
            Worker->>DB: UPDATE Documents SET status = failed, error_message = ...
        end
    end

    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    %% 4. RAG CHAT  (SSE streaming)
    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    rect rgb(245, 220, 255)
        Note over User,LF: 4 · RAG CHAT  (Server-Sent Events streaming)

        User->>FE: Open Chat page → New conversation
        FE->>API: POST /api/v1/chat/sessions  [Bearer JWT]
        API->>DB: INSERT ChatSessions (title = "New conversation")
        DB-->>API: { sessionId }
        API-->>FE: { session }

        User->>FE: Type question → Submit
        FE->>API: POST /api/v1/chat/sessions/:id/messages<br/>{ content }  Accept: text/event-stream
        API->>API: Zod: 1 ≤ content.length ≤ 10,000
        API->>DB: Verify session ownership (session_id + user_id)
        API->>DB: UPDATE ChatSessions SET title = content[0:60]
        Note right of DB: Title set from first message only
        API->>DB: INSERT ChatMessages (role = user)
        DB-->>API: userMessage row

        Note over API,FE: SSE connection opened
        API-->>FE: HTTP 200 + headers: text/event-stream
        API-->>FE: event: user_message  { message }
        FE-->>User: Render user bubble immediately

        Note over API,LF: RAG pipeline begins (packages/ai)
        API->>OpenAI: embedQuery(userQuery)<br/>model: text-embedding-3-small
        OpenAI-->>API: number[] (1536-dim query vector)

        API->>DB: SELECT dc.id, dc.content, d.name, dc.page_number,<br/>1-(embedding <=> ?)  AS similarity<br/>FROM DocumentChunks dc JOIN Documents d<br/>WHERE dc.user_id = ?  AND d.status = 'ready'<br/>AND similarity >= 0.3<br/>ORDER BY embedding <=> ? LIMIT 5
        Note right of DB: Cosine similarity via pgvector <=> operator<br/>Top-K = 5, threshold = 0.3
        DB-->>API: RetrievedChunk[] (up to 5 chunks)

        alt No chunks above similarity threshold
            API-->>FE: event: token  { token: "no docs message" }
            API-->>FE: event: done
            FE-->>User: "No relevant documents found" message
        else Chunks retrieved
            opt LangFuse keys configured
                API->>LF: lf.trace({ name: "rag-chat", userId })
                LF-->>API: traceId
                API->>LF: trace.generation({ name: "rag-generation", input: messages })
            end

            Note over API: buildContext(chunks)<br/>Format: [N] Document: "name", Page N\n{content}
            Note over API: Assemble LangChain messages:<br/>SystemMessage: HomeAtlas persona + citation rules<br/>HumanMessage: context block + Question: {userQuery}

            API->>LLM: llm.stream([SystemMessage, HumanMessage])
            Note right of LLM: Provider from LLM_PROVIDER env var<br/>maxTokens = 2048

            loop Token stream (until end-of-stream)
                LLM-->>API: StreamChunk (string token)
                API-->>FE: event: token  { token }
                FE-->>User: Append token to assistant bubble
            end

            API->>API: parseCitations(fullText, chunks)<br/>Regex [N] → { chunkId, documentId, documentName, page }
            API->>DB: INSERT ChatMessages<br/>(role = assistant, content, citations JSON,<br/>langfuse_trace_id)
            DB-->>API: assistantMessage row

            opt LangFuse configured
                API->>LF: generation.end({ output: fullText })
            end

            API-->>FE: event: done  { message: assistantMessage }
            FE-->>User: Render complete response + CitationChip components
        end
    end

    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    %% 5. DOCUMENT DOWNLOAD
    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    rect rgb(255, 255, 210)
        Note over User,R2: 5 · DOCUMENT DOWNLOAD
        User->>FE: Click download on document card
        FE->>API: GET /api/v1/documents/:id/download-url  [Bearer JWT]
        API->>DB: WHERE id = docId AND user_id = userId
        DB-->>API: Document row (+ r2_key)
        API->>R2: getSignedUrl(GetObjectCommand, 900s)
        R2-->>API: Presigned GET URL (15 min expiry)
        API-->>FE: { url }
        FE->>R2: GET <presigned URL>
        R2-->>FE: PDF stream
        FE-->>User: Browser downloads / opens PDF
    end

    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    %% 6. FEEDBACK
    %% ─────────────────────────────────────────
    rect rgb(235, 245, 235)
        Note over User,LF: 6 · RESPONSE FEEDBACK  (thumbs up / down)
        User->>FE: Click 👍 or 👎 on assistant message
        FE->>API: POST /api/v1/chat/messages/:id/feedback<br/>{ value: 1 | -1 }
        API->>DB: WHERE id = messageId AND user_id = userId AND role = assistant
        DB-->>API: Message row (with langfuse_trace_id)
        API->>DB: UPDATE ChatMessages SET feedback = value
        opt LangFuse configured AND traceId present
            API->>LF: lf.score({ traceId, name: "user-feedback", value })
            Note right of LF: Non-fatal — failure silently ignored
        end
        API-->>FE: { ok: true }
        FE-->>User: Feedback icon fills / confirms
    end
